         </extensionElements>
      </group>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-8B15C1EB-2CA2-4824-B970-69F68D9441BB" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
            <signavio:signavioLabel bold="" fill="" fontFamily="" fontSize="18.0" italic="" ref="text-left"/>
            <signavio:signavioLabel bold="" fill="" fontFamily="" fontSize="18.0" italic="" ref="text-right"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>1. CBAs need prior BU approval before changing NCNR order  (Pushouts, Cancellation requests). CBA can override NCNR order.
2. NCNR Setting can be applied at Sales Order Header/Line-Item Level
3. Cancellation Window represents number of days prior to either CDD or CGID when customer can no longer cancel or push out their order
4. Cancellation windows controls production cycle.
5. Business maintains the cancellation window check criteria
6. If cancellation window checks fails, customer can not change order.
</text>
      </textAnnotation>
   </process>
